    <item>
      <title>DESCRIPTIVE TEXT</title>
      <link>http://ekstrover.github.io/writing/het-descriptive-intro/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://ekstrover.github.io/writing/het-descriptive-intro/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;header class=&#39;material-header material-writing&#39;&gt;
&lt;ul class=&#39;material-specs&#39;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Skill:&lt;/b&gt; Writing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Grade:&lt;/b&gt; 2nd Grade of SMP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Text:&lt;/b&gt; Descriptive Text&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Creator:&lt;/b&gt; Heti Ratnasari&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Goal:&lt;/b&gt; Writing a descriptive text&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;material-body&#34;&gt;
&lt;h1 class=&#39;text-center&#39;&gt;DESCRIPTIVE TEXT&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Purpose:&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;
To describe or inform a particular thing to the reader. It can be person, plant, animal, etc.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Generic Structure:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;- Identification :&lt;/b&gt; this part will describe us about general information of the topic.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;- Description :&lt;/b&gt; this part will describe us about specific information of the topic.
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Tenses:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br&gt;When you write a descriptive text, you have to use simple present tense.&lt;br&gt;
Look at the picture of Descriptive Text Organizer &lt;a class=&#34;link-source&#34; href=&#34;www.decantresswine.com&#34;&gt;Source &amp;rarr;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;img style=&#34;width:100%&#34; src=&#34;http://ekstrover.github.io/media/writing/het/het-descriptive-intro-1.jpg&#34;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Here is the example in writing a descriptive text.&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;a class=&#34;link-source&#34; href=&#34;www.slideshare.net&#34;&gt;Source &amp;rarr;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;img style=&#34;width:100%&#34; src=&#34;http://ekstrover.github.io/media/writing/het/het-descriptive-intro-2.jpg&#34;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Here, I have a descriptive plan sheet. (*you can download the sheet in pdf file on the website)&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;!-- ( www.slideshare.net ) --&gt;
&lt;img style=&#34;width:100%&#34; src=&#34;http://ekstrover.github.io/media/writing/het/het-descriptive-intro-3.jpg&#34;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
In this descriptive plan sheet, you can write or list the characteristic of your pet. Remember about the generic structures of descriptive text. It should be identification first, then description.
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Firstly, I write my descriptive plan at the work sheet. From that work sheet we will know what the characteristic of our pet is, what its hobby is, what its color is, etc. I will give you the example about descriptive text entitled &amp;ldquo;my cat&amp;rdquo;. Here is my descriptive text based on the list I have.
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img style=&#34;width:100%&#34; src=&#34;http://ekstrover.github.io/media/writing/het/het-descriptive-intro-4.jpg&#34;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
In order to help us in writing or composing the descriptive text properly, we have to list what we will describe about the topic first. Then we can write or compose the descriptive text in a good structure.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;tombol -complete&#34; href=&#34;http://ekstrover.github.io/writing/het-descriptive-task-1&#34;&gt;Go to Task 1&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
