      <guid>http://ekstrover.github.io/writing/din-recount-intro/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;header class=&#39;material-header material-writing&#39;&gt;
&lt;ul class=&#39;material-specs&#39;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Skill:&lt;/b&gt; Writing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Level:&lt;/b&gt; Beginner - Intermediate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Text:&lt;/b&gt; Recount Text&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Theme:&lt;/b&gt; Holiday&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Goal:&lt;/b&gt; Writing a Recount Text&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Compiled by:&lt;/b&gt; Dinda Anggi N. S.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;material-body&#34;&gt;
&lt;h1 class=&#39;text-center&#39;&gt;Recount Text&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Purpose:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To retell or inform something that happened in the past and to tell a series of past event.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Generic Structure:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
-   Orientation&lt;br/&gt;
-   Events&lt;br/&gt;
-   Conclusion
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Tenses:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Remember that in writing a recount text, you will use &lt;b&gt;simple past tense&lt;/b&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Look at the picture of Recount (Text Organizer)&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;http://ekstrover.github.io/media/writing/din/din-recount-intro-1.jpg&#34;&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link-source&#34; href=&#34;https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/736x/a8/52/6b/a8526b8eaa730c31f4e4748878e3c6f6.jpg&#34;&gt;Image Source &amp;rarr;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Here is the example in writing a recount text.&lt;br&gt;I have a recount plan sheet. Here it is.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;http://ekstrover.github.io/media/writing/din/din-recount-intro-2.jpg&#34;&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link-source&#34; href=&#34;https://docs.google.com/file/d/0BwNLh47Up8pHZWdDTVlyX3ZWbDQ/edit&#34;&gt;Credit &amp;rarr;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link-source&#34; href=&#34;http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-vJcNyeAdsLQ/UX-4dLphW1I/AAAAAAAAGo0/Y2yKjtMfUII/s1600/holidayrecountpic02.jpg&#34;&gt;Image Source &amp;rarr;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Before writing a recount text, I write my recount plan at that sheet. From that recount plan, we can write when we went, with who we went there, where we went, and what we did. I will give you the example about the story of my holiday in Jogja.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;http://ekstrover.github.io/media/writing/din/din-recount-intro-3.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link-source&#34; href=&#34;https://docs.google.com/file/d/0BwNLh47Up8pHZWdDTVlyX3ZWbDQ/edit&#34;&gt;Material Adaption Source &amp;rarr;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;By writing the recount plan first, it will help us in writing the recount text easily as we have listed all of the things that we should add if we want to write a recount text, like the place, the time, and the activities.
Here is the example of recount text based on the recount plan that I made before.
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
